# Planlet UI preferences

Canonical philosophy: **`docs/DESIGN_PHILOSOPHY.md`**. Audit UI changes against it before completion.

Keep Planlet aligned with these design principles:

- **Content first** — when content and chrome compete, prefer content
- **When in doubt, remove** — every control must earn its place
- **Interfaces disappear** — no permanent instructional hints users quickly learn
- **Information once** — no duplicated titles, sources, filters, or metadata
- **Progressive disclosure** — frequent actions visible; occasional in More; rare in Settings
- **Mobile-first** — thumb-friendly spacing; drawers closed by default; cards dominate
- **Calm reading** — soft hierarchy, restrained chips, truncated previews, “Show more”
- **Shared components** — reuse Read Aloud, Archive, More, Flashcards patterns

## Life Lab

When improving Life Lab, prioritize **clarity and readability** over adding visible features.

List pages: compact cards, filtered previews, capped chips, grouped “Show more”.
Detail pages: structured content and progressive sections; keep the default view calm.

Match existing patterns in `components/life-lab/` and `lib/life-lab/card-preview.ts`.
